# Copy to the project root as  .client-demo.env  and edit, then:
#   ./setupclientdemo
#
# Join your phone’s hotspot as a client and use a fixed IPv4 (stable URL for QR).
#
# Android hotspot: WPA2. Many devices use 192.168.43.0/24 + gw 192.168.43.1, but *not* all
#— plenty use 10.x.x.x (or other RFC1918). If static IP fails, join once on DHCP, run
#  ./scripts/detect-client-demo-subnet.sh
# and set CLIENT_DEMO_GW / CLIENT_DEMO_IPV4 to match, or re-run setup-client-wifi.sh (it
# auto-aligns from the live lease when the env is wrong). (iPhone: different subnet; see
# comments under CLIENT_DEMO_IPV4.)
#
# Hotspot password: most Android and iPhone personal hotspots use WPA2 (not “open”). If
# setup fails with “Secrets were required”, set CLIENT_DEMO_PSK. Leave PSK empty only for a
# genuinely open (no key) network.
# CLIENT_DEMO_PSK=
# (alias) CLIENT_DEMO_PASSWORD=
#
# --- Your hotspot SSID (must match the phone) ---
CLIENT_DEMO_SSID=Sophia Science Project
#
# NetworkManager connection name (no spaces; safe on disk)
CLIENT_DEMO_CONN_NAME=smartair-client
#
# Wi‑Fi interface (Raspberry Pi is usually wlan0; USB Wi‑Fi might be wlan1)
CLIENT_DEMO_IFACE=
#
# Static IPv4 (must match the *same* subnet and gateway as the hotspot).
# Android: often 192.168.43.1/24 — example below. 10.x and other ranges are common; use
# detect-client-demo-subnet.sh on DHCP, or let setup-client-wifi.sh auto-align after connect.
# iPhone / iPad: usually 172.20.10.0/28 — not 192.168.43.x
# CLIENT_DEMO_HOST_LAST=200   # last octet for /24 when auto-aligning (default 200)
# CLIENT_DEMO_DISABLE_AUTO_ALIGN=0   # set to 1 to force the addresses in this file (debug)
CLIENT_DEMO_IPV4=192.168.43.100/24
CLIENT_DEMO_GW=192.168.43.1
CLIENT_DEMO_DNS=192.168.43.1
#
# Linux account that owns the project (the systemd service runs as this user).
# Leave unset for auto-detect: the user who runs ./setupclientdemo (SUDO_USER), or first uid 1000.
# If you see "user pi does not exist", set to your login: run `whoami` (e.g. raspberry, or the name you chose on first boot).
# CLIENT_DEMO_USER=
#
# Full URL for notes / QR (optional; used by generate-demo-qrs if you add hooks later)
# CLIENT_DEMO_URL=http://192.168.43.100:5001/
#
# App port (must match config.yaml server.port; default 5001; used for QR if set)
# SMARTAIR_PORT=5001
